# AI chat (OpenRouter + AI SDK)

## API route (`app/api/chat/route.ts`)

- OpenRouter via `createOpenAI({ apiKey, baseURL: 'https://openrouter.ai/api/v1' })`
- Model id from `process.env.OPENROUTER_MODEL` with code fallback
- `streamText` + `convertToModelMessages` from `ai`
- Response: `result.toUIMessageStreamResponse()`
- `export const runtime = 'edge'`

Keep the **English teacher** system prompt tone: friendly, brief grammar corrections, encouraging.

## Client (`app/page.tsx`)

- `useChat()` from `@ai-sdk/react` (default `/api/chat`)
- Messages use **`parts`** (UI message format), not legacy `content` string only:

```tsx
parts.map(p => (p.type === 'text' ? p.text : '')).join('')
```

- Status: `ready` | `submitted` | `streaming` — disable input while loading
- `sendMessage({ text: input })` for user turns

## Auth boundary

`proxy.ts` returns **401 JSON** for `/api/chat` when session is invalid. UI should surface `error` from `useChat` gracefully.

## Adding features

- New tools or models: change route only; keep env vars documented in README
- Do not expose `OPENROUTER_API_KEY` to the client
